Both files are written and `transcript.json` validates against `transcript_schema.json` (25 iterations).

**Headline finding:** Among six treatment indicators, only `treatment_enzalutamide` affects `objective_response`, and its benefit is concentrated in the joint subgroup `mcrpc=0 AND brca2_mutation=0 AND ar_v7_positive=0 AND msi_high=0` (response 79.8% vs 17.2%, +62.6 percentage points). Each of the four markers individually nullifies the effect. Stratified, interaction-model, and tree-based CATE searches all converged on the same four-predicate rule. Olaparib in BRCA2+, pembrolizumab in MSI-high, and lu177-PSMA in PSMA-high all showed no benefit.
